730321f-a.title: General view - Amsterdam Avenue - Southwest and Northwest.
730321f-a.text:
Amsterdam Avenue, at W. 138th Street, (general view southwest
and northwest).
A set of two views from a roof-top in the ''Heights'' area of
upper Manhattan. View. No. 1 is southwestward down the river to
show at 122nd Street, the Riverside Church and Grants Tohb, No. 2
is northwestward to show the George Washington Bridge at 181st
Street. In the background of both views is the dimly outlined
JJersey shore.
August 1935
Views: 1 -2
R. W. Hill
MAY BE REPRODUCED

731418f-a.title: Colleges and Universities - College of the City of New York.
731418f-a.text:
College of te City of New York:
Amsterdam Ave., at the S.E. corner of West 138th Street. Shown is
an entrance to the Lewisohn Stadium of the College of the City of New York.
This view taken before a Municipal Concert.
August 25, 1935.
R.w. Rili.
